   Kuehne is covered by the New Jersey Toxic Catastrophe Prevention Act (TCPA ? NJAC 7:31).  The  regulated substance handled at this site is chlorine.
   We implement our accidental release prevention policy to ensure compliance with both EPA RMP and NJ TCPA.  The accidental release prevention program includes:
?       Process Safety Information, which includes an MSDS sheets for chlorine, safety information for the chlorine system and process chemistry for chlorine and sodium hydroxide; inventory which is an ongoing update of chlorine quantities on hand; Flow Diagrams, these are detailed drawings of the piping, instrumentation and process flow, repackaging flow, piping and instrumentation symbols; Piping Isometric Diagrams and Material Specification sheets, these include detailed drawings of the sodium hypochlorite manufacturing facility, chlorine repackaging facility, tank car unloading and distribution piping, chlorine venting system and the bi-gas system; Design Code and Standards including various publications of The Chlorine Institute manuals and other indexes and handbooks; Electrical One Line Diagrams which are detailed drawings of all the electrical wiring throughout the facility; Firewater Piping System this states that our facility has no dedicated fire water piping system.  Local officials have approved the size and type of our fire extinguishers as being adequate; Sewer System Diagrams, stating these diagrams are not included.
?       Hazard Analysis/Risk Assessment, this includes process hazard analysis for the chlorine system.  It presents different release scenarios and the area effected by them; 
?       Standard Operating Procedures which include detailed instructions on chlorine repackaging, hypochlorite manufacturing and inspection procedures of chlorine tank trucks; 
?       Incident/Accident Investigations and Procedures which is a list of all accidents or near miss occurrences, that also includes follow-up documentation of corrective actions; 
?       Emerg

ency Response Procedures which is our emergency response plan; 
?       Training including the bleach operator training guide, records and tabulation; Annual Calendar Year Tabulation ?Training?, Topographic Maps covering Elizabeth, Orange, Weehawken, and Jersey City, NJ; Site Plant; 
?       Mechanical Integrity program, which includes our preventative maintenance procedures and records; Annual Tabulation of EHS Equipment; 
?       Audit Procedures and Reports which includes our risk management checklist and program.
   Our emergency response policies are documented in the Standard Operating Procedures and reviewed with the employees annually.  They include, location of the company?s Emergency Response Plan, a general site plan indicating the locations of Extraordinarily Hazardous Substances, Material Safety Data Sheets, location of atmospheric monitoring equipment, location of two way radio equipment, location of portable battery powered lanterns, location of emergency event log book, available equipment such as leak kits and heavy machinery and location of first aid kits, training provided to all employees and frequency of emergency response drills.
   There are employees trained in emergency response.  They have periodic drills and assessments of how to mitigate and stop a chlorine release on site, chlorine release off site, sodium and potassium hydroxide solution spills, sodium hypochlorite solution spills, fires and explosions.
   The general accidental release prevention program includes routine maintenance checks of equipment, containment vessels and safety measures that are in place.
   There have been no accidents in the last five years requiring reporting in the five-year accident history
   The main planned change to improve safety is the ongoing security analysis, and implementation of security measures and devices such as the strategic placement of surveillance cameras around the facility.
